SIMPLE: rookery
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rookery
<hw>Rook"er*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Rookeries</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The breeding
place of a colony of rooks; also, the birds themselves.</def>
<rj><au>Tennyson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A breeding place of other gregarious birds, as of
herons, penguins, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The breeding ground of seals, esp. of the fur
seals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A dilapidated building with many rooms and
occupants; a cluster of dilapidated or mean buildings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>A brothel.</def> <mark>[Low]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rooky</ent>⟦br⟧
